    "read": "The selected-tile split is correct at S128 and usable as a diagnostic, but it is not a speedup candidate at the hard S4096 layer-2 route. K128 is slower than both the sparse-atomic gate and the seq-tile compact partial store. K256 reduces the partial stream versus K128 but still loses to sparse atomics, and only roughly ties the older compact-partial rung once final fold is counted.",
